Laguna has one of the highest adolescent pregnancy in the Philippines. According to the Global Youth Monitoring Report, have the highest rate of teenage pregnancy in the country. Over-all, about 1 in 10 high school girls nationally, about 360,000 Filipino girls in total, will get pregnant by the time they finish high school. But Laguna’s rate is the highest, almost 1 in 5 girls, or more than 21% of the girls.Few medical centers offer family planning services to the indigenous peoples in Laguna. But less than 18% of women ever visited the nearest health center, and 45% of indigenous health centers lack a trained person in handling family planning methods. Compounding this problem is the lack of family planning services and negligence of young people’s reproductive health concerns.
